Introduction

xikers, formerly known as KQ Fellaz 2, is a ten-member boy group under KQ Entertainment. The group officially debuted on March 30, 2023, with the mini album "HOUSE OF TRICKY: Doorbell Ringing."

Their group name "xikers" is a combination of "x" which represents coordinates and "hikers" which means travelers as the group members are traveling through time and space to find the coordinates.

The name of the fandom, "roadùì®" is inspired by the word "hikers" from xikers's group name, and combines the "road" that "hikers" use with "ùì®", indicating the horizontal y-axis.

On May 10, it was announced that xikers would make their Japanese debut with the single "Tsuki (Lunatic)" on August 7, 2024.
